[4] Honduras
Date: Sun 2 Sep 2007
Source:Prensa Latina [edited]
<http://www.plenglish.com/article.asp?ID=%7BACDC7E3B-6CC6-40C9-9AB6-F152802997CB%7D&language=EN>

Honduran Dengue Fever Crisis Worsens
-----------------------------------------
The expansion of dengue fever in Honduras is reaching [levels] of a
national crisis, since almost 1600 new cases were registered last
week [27-31 Aug 2007], most of them in the capital [Tegucigalpa].
Despite the effort of health authorities, there are unhealthy sectors
in the city, and negligence also facilitates the appearance of new
[breeding sites] for _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes.
Statistics from the Honduran Public Health Ministry said 8 people
have died as a consequence of dengue fever. The classical variety of
the disease has affected 16 878 people, and the hemorrhagic one, 823 people.
Local newspaper El Heraldo reported more than 50 percent of the cases
appeared in the capital, where it was questioned that the yellow
alert [should] be maintained, despite the number of affected people.
Honduran Public Health Minister Jenny Meza admitted the struggle
should be intensified, but she demanded greater compliance with
cleaning measures and instructions.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett
