[5] Philippines (Laguna)
Date: Fri 24 Aug 2007
Source: Inquirer.net [edited]
<http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/inquirerheadlines/regions/view_article.php?article_id=84386>

Dengue cases [in] Laguna
------------------------
The provincial health office in Laguna reported 223 new dengue
victims in August [2007], or a 36-percent increase compared to the
July [2007] figure.
As of this month [August 2007], the total number of victims reported
since January [2007] has increased to 846 from 623 in July, said Dr.
Alfaneo Lagos, provincial health office chief.
Over the same period, the total number of dengue fatalities increased
to 8, up by 2 from a total of 6 recorded in July [2007].
[Byline: Romulo Ponte]
--
Communicated by:
Promed Rapporteur Brent Barrett
