[6] Philippines (Iloilo City)
Date: Tue 28 Aug 2007
Source: Cebu, Philippines [edited]
<http://visayas.wowphilippines.com/iloilo/2007/08/28/11-dengue-deaths-recorded-in-iloilo-city/>

Dengue fever cases in Iloilo City continue to increase in number,
with 11 deaths already reported as of this August [2007]. The latest
report, submitted by Dr. Mae Delmo, City Health Office (CHO), focal
[contact] person for the disease, to Mayor Jerry Trenas, showed that
44 of the city's 180 barangays [subdivisions] are already affected by dengue.
For this month alone [August 2007], the report showed that there were
68 dengue cases, which is some 20 percent higher compared to the 14
cases monitored in August 2006. From January to August this year
[2007], dengue cases here already totalled 189. The figure is 50-60
percent higher compared to the 96 cases during the same period last year.
There were 10 recorded deaths pending the filing of the death
certificate of a grade school pupil from Arevalo district who died
last Sunday [26 Aug 2007] due to dengue. The confirmation of the said
death will bring to 11 the number of dengue deaths and 190 cases in the city.
There were only 4 dengue deaths recorded in 2006.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett
