[8] Viet Nam
Date: Mon 27 Sep 2007
Source: Viet Nam Net [edited]
<http://english.vietnamnet.vn/social/2007/08/734352/>

According to the Health Ministry, Viet Nam has had 52 107 cases of
dengue fever so far this year [2007], including 49 deaths. Southern
provinces comprising Tien Giang, Dong Thap, An Giang, Kien Giang and
Soc Trang have witnessed the highest numbers of dengue fever patients.
According to health experts, the number of dengue fever cases this
year is the highest since 1999. [In 1998 the country had 230 000
cases, the highest level in the past 10 years].
The Health Ministry has set up 6 working groups to evaluate the
dengue fever situation in 17 southern, 4 central and 3 northern
provinces of high risk. The ministry has also provided 3000 liters
[792.5 gallons] of anti-mosquito chemical for the HCM City Pasteur
Institute to kill mosquitoes in the south, and 2670 liters [705.3
gallons] of solution to cure dengue fever for provinces of high risk
[prevent cases by vector mosquito control, not cure them. - Mod.TY].
--
