[9]China (Guangdong)
Date: Thu 6 Sep 2007
Source:China Daily [edited]
<http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2007-09/06/content_6087035.htm>

A total of 25 people have been confirmed to have contracted dengue
fever in Zhuhai, a city in South China's Guangdong Province, in the
last 2 weeks, the city's vice mayor Deng Qunfang said on Thursday [6
Aug 2007]. The outbreak of dengue was found in 3 localities in the
city. Local health authorities have also found another 16 suspected
cases since 22 Aug [2007], Deng said.
Deng attributed the outbreak to the rainy weather which favored
mosquito reproduction but said the outbreak had been brought under
control. The city set up an emergency headquarters to fight the
disease on Wednesday [5 Sep 2007] and has launched a mass campaign to
clean up the city and kill mosquitoes.
The number of imported cases of [this?] potentially fatal,
mosquito-borne disease has been rising year by year and there have
been several local outbreaks in recent years.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett
